Sentencas: In this work, we investigated the long-term oxidation behavior of a Ni-Fe (1:1 wt ratio) support for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications.
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of a Ni-Fe support in SOFC anode atmosphere

Sentencas: Ni-Fe supports were obtained through tape casting, high temperature sintering and pre-reducing in 97% H-2/N-2(9/91)-3% H2O at 750 and 1000 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of a Ni-Fe support in SOFC anode atmosphere

Sentencas: Then the Ni-Fe supports were exposed in simulated anode atmospheres of H-2/N-2 (9/91)-3% H2O and 75% H-2/N-2(9/ 91)-25% H2O for periods of up to 1000 hat 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of a Ni-Fe support in SOFC anode atmosphere

Sentencas: The samples were examined for mass change, phase and chemical composition, and microstructure evolution during the annealing process.
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of a Ni-Fe support in SOFC anode atmosphere

Sentencas: The Ni-Fe supports exposed to H-2/N-2-3% H2O showed negligible oxidation, while those exposed to H-2/N-2-25% H2O showed a 4-6% mass increase, due to the fact that a Fe-rich oxide scale was found on the surface of the Ni-Fe alloy particles.
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of a Ni-Fe support in SOFC anode atmosphere

Sentencas: Room-temperature conductivity measurements showed that the supports annealed in the two atmospheres maintained sufficiently high conductivity.
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of a Ni-Fe support in SOFC anode atmosphere

Sentencas: The results from the current work demonstrate that the porous Ni-Fe support can be well employed in SOFCs, especially metal-supported SOFCs.
Titulo: Oxidation behavior of a Ni-Fe support in SOFC anode atmosphere
